2016.10.27, piff, ripreso versione da "IKM Oracle Incremental Update" e customizzata per eseguire: - select / insert diretto - no update Serve per velocizzare gli inserts dove vi Ã¨ una grosse mole di dati (es. nelle procedure di load nella D_XXXX_MAP_RES)

Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface
Commit all data inserted or updated in the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target table.

This option affects the use of PURGE key word and the way statistics are collected:
Values PURGE STATS 10 Yes DBMS_STATS 9 No DBMS_STATS 8 No ANALYZE

Valid values are - MINUS: The MINUS clause uses the Minus set operator when populating the flow table. This clause is used to exclude identical records already existing in the target. - NOT_EXISTS: The NOT EXISTS clause uses the Not Exists set operator when populating the flow table. This clause is used to exclude identical records already existing in the target. - POST_FLOW: all records from source are loaded into flow table. After that an update statement is used to flag all rows in flow table, which identically exist in target. - NONE: all records from source are loaded into flow table. All target records are updated even when target records is identical to flow table record.
Check this option if you wish to analyze the target table before loading data into the integration table.
Use this option to specify the hint to be used while loading the integration table.
